						               													<description>Reversal is a Reversi game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is mixed elements of shogi pieces. Some tiles can be flipped over by pinching both ends of the tiles, while others have a unique way of flipping over. It is hard to decide which tile to use and when. It is a game where reversals occur with every move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two main types of tiles:&amp;#10;Normal tiles: Tiles are turned over if the end of the row or column is a tile of your color, just like in reversi.&amp;#10;Ability tiles: Tiles are turned over in the direction of the &amp;quot;&amp;#226;&amp;#150;&amp;#178;&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;line&amp;quot; on the tile.&amp;#10;The color of the tile to be flipped over is not distinguished.&amp;#10;If your ability tile is flipped over, you lose points and it becomes a tile of your opponent's color, but you can find the difference.&amp;#10;Also, each ability tile has its own points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two rules you can play by&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(1) Point rule&amp;#10;At the end of the game, the player with the higher point total of the ability tiles of his/her color that are turned over wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(2) Majority Rule&amp;#10;The player with the highest number of tiles of his/her color on the table at the end of the game wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
